    "ts": "2026-04-21T21:34:00+00:00",
    "headline": "Prudential Extends Suspension of New Business In Japan. The Stock Is Falling.",
    "summary": "Prudential Financial  Japan affiliate has voluntarily extended a suspension of new sales in that market by another 180 days to have additional time to complete governance and other reforms.  Prudential of Japan on Tuesday said the extension “reflects POJ’s determination that additional time is needed to complete foundational reforms to its compensation structure, governance, sales oversight, and broader operating model.”  Japan remains a core market, a spokesperson told Barron’s, but Prudential “will not resume new sales until there is confidence that POJ’s compliance, oversight, and governance environment supports doing so responsibly.”",
